			<div class="article-correspondence layout-item fill-pattern-light">
		<div class="layout-item-intro">
			<h2>Correspondence</h2>
			<a class="xsmall link-alt" href="https://www.thesunmagazine.org/letter-to-the-editor">Write a Letter to the Editor&nbsp;&#9656;</a>
		</div>

		<div id="article-correspondences" class="correspondences correspondences-collapsed">
								<div class="block-correspondence" id="2393">
		<blockquote class="quote-2">
			<p>I had to write after reading Gordon Grice&rsquo;s &ldquo;<a href="/article/2150">After the Stillbirth</a>&rdquo; [October 1999]. In 1985, I had an ectopic pregnancy that ruptured my fallopian tube. I hadn&rsquo;t known I was pregnant, and was devastated when I came out of surgery and found out what had happened. That I was single made no difference; this would have been a much wanted child.</p>

<p>I lived in the South then, with many relatives nearby. My mother urged me not to tell any of them that I had been pregnant. &ldquo;Just tell them you had some female problems,&rdquo; she said. This seemed outrageous to me, and I asked whom she thought she was protecting. &ldquo;You,&rdquo; she replied over and over. Finally, she admitted, &ldquo;All right, it&rsquo;s me.&rdquo;</p>

<p>My aunts showed up, as they do whenever a relative is in the hospital, hovering over me, wanting answers but never asking outright. I felt no shame and told them the truth. In their eyes, this was just another thing for which to condemn me. I was already divorced, a flight attendant, and drove a sports car.</p>

<p>My grief lasted for years. Some friends said, &ldquo;It wasn&rsquo;t a real baby.&rdquo; Maybe that was true for them, but for me my miscarriage was the loss of a human being. That is why Grice&rsquo;s essay struck me so deeply. I admire how he was able to articulate his pain. As one who has been there, I know: everyone has to grieve in his or her own way.</p>
							<p class="quote-2-author">Linda Simmons Monroe<br>Charlotte, North Carolina</p>
					</blockquote>
	</div>

					</div>

			</div>
    
		<div class="article-correspondence-cta">
		<div class="cta cta-l1" data-url="https://www.thesunmagazine.org/letter-to-the-editor">
			<div class="cta-intro">
				<h5 class="cta-title alt-ff">Thinking about writing us a letter?</h5>
				<p class="cta-text">Give in to the temptation. We love getting mail. <br><span class="xsmall">(Of course, we reserve the right to edit.)</span></p>
			</div>
			<a href="https://www.thesunmagazine.org/letter-to-the-editor" class="cta-button b b-4 b-padding-tight small" data-label="Write Us A Letter!">Write Us A Letter!</a>
		</div>
	</div>
	

